description: The Invesco BulletShares 2026 Corporate Bond ETF (Fund) is based on the Invesco BulletShares Corporate Bond 2026 Index (Index). The Fund will invest atleast 80% of its total assets in corporate bonds that comprise the Index. The Index seeks to measure the performance of a portfolio of US dollar-denominated investment grade corporate bonds with maturities or effective maturities in 2026. The Fund does not purchase all of the securities in the Index; instead, the Fund utilizes a "sampling" methodology to seek to achieve its investment objective. The Fund and the Index are rebalanced monthly. The Fund has a designated year of maturity of 2026 and will terminate on or about Dec. 15, 2026. See the prospectus for more information.Effective Jan. 1, 2024, the Underlying Index name changed from the Nasdaq BulletShares USD Corporate Bond 2026 Index to the Invesco BulletShares Corporate Bond 2026 Index. See the prospectus for more information.
name: Invesco BulletShares 2026 Corporate Bond ETF
